---
title: Bone-In Pork Chops and Stuffed Pupusa-Inspired Flatbreads with Curtido-Style Slaw
description: Pupusas are traditionally made with pre-cooked corn flour, similar to masa harina. Here, we are combining all-purpose flour and golden cornmeal to form a smooth, easy-to-work-with dough. Stuff each ball of dough with melty mozzarella cheese and cook until golden on both sides.

